                             fuzz-systemctl-parse-argv -runs=100.                                                                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             A double-free vulnerability was detected in the `parse_path_argument` function of the systemd codebase. When fuzzing the `systemctl_parse_argv` entry point,                        
                             AddressSanitizer flagged an attempt to free the same heap buffer twice: once within `parse_path_argument` and again during the static teardown in the fuzz harness.                 
                             The issue manifests as an `ERROR: AddressSanitizer: attempting double-free` abort.                                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Issue                                                                                                                                                                             
                               AddressSanitizer reports a double-free on a 16-byte heap allocation at address `0x502000007310`. The first free occurs in `parse_path_argument` (in                               
                             `src/shared/parse-argument.c:68`), and the second free takes place in the fuzz harnesss `static_destruct` call (in `src/basic/static-destruct.h:95`), which runs                   
                             after `systemctl_parse_argv`.                                                                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Vulnerability Type                                                                                                                                                                
                               This is a classic double-free vulnerability. Double-free errors can lead to use-after-free, heap corruption, or arbitrary code execution if exploited.                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Key Observations                                                                                                                                                                  
                                The faulty allocation happens via `realloc` in `path_extend_internal` (in `src/basic/path-util.c:585`) when making a path absolute.                                             
                                `parse_path_argument` takes ownership of the buffer returned by `path_make_absolute_cwd` and unconditionally frees it.                                                          
                                The fuzzing harness registers the same buffer for static destruction, causing a second free when the harness cleans up.                                                         
                                The crash stack traces consistently show the two frees in `parse_path_argument` and `static_destruct`, confirming the double-free.                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Impacted Code Areas                                                                                                                                                               
                               To fully understand and assess the vulnerability you should review:                                                                                                               
                               1. `src/shared/parse-argument.c` (the implementation of `parse_path_argument`, especially the free logic).                                                                        
                               2. `src/basic/path-util.c` (allocation logic in `path_extend_internal` and `path_make_absolute_cwd`).                                                                             
                               3. `src/systemctl/systemctl.c` (`systemctl_parse_argv` which invokes `parse_path_argument`).                                                                                      
                               4. The fuzzing harness in `src/systemctl/fuzz-systemctl-parse-argv.c`, particularly how it registers buffers for static destruction.                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             This issue is surfaced when exercising `systemctl_parse_argv` via the libFuzzer harness, but the root cause resides in the memory ownership and free logic in the                   
                             shared parsing utilities.                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log

                             ===Analysis Report===                                                                                                                                                               
                             # Analysis Report                                                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Relevant Code Snippets                                                                                                                                                           
                             <code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             src/shared/parse-argument.c:55-81                                                                                                                                                   
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             55:int parse_path_argument(const char *path, bool suppress_root, char **arg) {                                                                                                      
                             56:        char *p;                                                                                                                                                                 
                             57:        int r;                                                                                                                                                                   
                             58:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             59:        /*                                                                                                                                                                       
                             60:         * This function is intended to be used in command line parsers, to handle paths that are passed                                                                         
                             61:         * in. It makes the path absolute, and reduces it to NULL if omitted or root (the latter optionally).                                                                    
                             62:         *                                                                                                                                                                       
                             63:         * NOTE THAT THIS WILL FREE THE PREVIOUS ARGUMENT POINTER ON SUCCESS!                                                                                                    
                             64:         * Hence, do not pass in uninitialized pointers.                                                                                                                         
                             65:         */                                                                                                                                                                      
                             66:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             67:        if (isempty(path)) {                                                                                                                                                     
                             68:                *arg = mfree(*arg);                                                                                                                                              
                             69:                return 0;                                                                                                                                                        
                             70:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             71:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             72:        r = path_make_absolute_cwd(path, &p);                                                                                                                                    
                             73:        if (r < 0)                                                                                                                                                               
                             74:                return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to parse path \"%s\" and make it absolute: %m", path);                                                                         
                             75:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             76:        path_simplify(p);                                                                                                                                                        
                             77:        if (suppress_root && empty_or_root(p))                                                                                                                                   
                             78:                p = mfree(p);                                                                                                                                                    
                             79:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             80:        return free_and_replace(*arg, p);                                                                                                                                        
                             81:}                                                                                                                                                                                
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             src/basic/static-destruct.h:86-105                                                                                                                                                  
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             86:static inline void static_destruct(void) {                                                                                                                                       
                             87:        if (!__start_SYSTEMD_STATIC_DESTRUCT)                                                                                                                                    
                             88:                return;                                                                                                                                                          
                             89:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             90:        for (const StaticDestructor *d = ALIGN_PTR(__start_SYSTEMD_STATIC_DESTRUCT);                                                                                             
                             91:             d < __stop_SYSTEMD_STATIC_DESTRUCT;                                                                                                                                 
                             92:             d = ALIGN_PTR(d + 1))                                                                                                                                               
                             93:                switch (d->type) {                                                                                                                                               
                             94:                case STATIC_DESTRUCTOR_SIMPLE:                                                                                                                                   
                             95:                        d->simple.destroy(d->simple.data);                                                                                                                       
                             96:                        break;                                                                                                                                                   
                             97:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             98:                case STATIC_DESTRUCTOR_ARRAY:                                                                                                                                    
                             99:                        array_cleanup(&d->array);                                                                                                                                
                             100:                        break;                                                                                                                                                  
                             101:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             102:                default:                                                                                                                                                        
                             103:                        assert_not_reached();                                                                                                                                   
                             104:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             105:}                                                                                                                                                                               
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Analyze the Root Cause                                                                                                                                                           
                                - The doublefree occurs because `parse_path_argument()` both unconditionally frees the old `*arg` (via `mfree()` or via `free_and_replace()`) *and* the same                    
                             pointer is registered for cleanup in the staticdestructor list (the fuzz harness calls `static_destruct()` after each run). When `static_destruct()` later invokes                 
                             `freep(&arg_root)` (or `freep(&arg_image)`), it calls `free()` on the same buffer a second time, triggering AddressSanitizers doublefree error.                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Preservation of Critical Logic                                                                                                                                                   
                                - We must preserve the existing behavior of:                                                                                                                                     
                                   Turning a CLI path argument into an absolute, simplified path.                                                                                                             
                                   Freeing/replacing the old argument buffer on each invocation of `parse_path_argument()`.                                                                                     
                                   Registering the final argument buffer for static teardown, so normal systemd shutdown continues to clean up.                                                                 
                                - We must *not* adjust or remove the fuzz harness, nor modify staticdestruct logic, nor skip freeing in genuine systemd usecases.                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Strategy: Delay the Static Destructor Cleanup Until Finalization                                                                                                                 
                                - Rather than deregister or awkwardly clear the staticdestruct entry at each `parse_path_argument()`, we will prevent the static teardown from freeing an                       
                             inflight argument that has already been freed earlier in the same invocation.                                                                                                      
                                - Concretely, in `parse_path_argument()`:                                                                                                                                        
                                  a) After successfully replacing or freeing `*arg`, record that the staticdestructor entry for this argument has already been handled for the current                        
                             invocation.                                                                                                                                                                         
                                  b) On subsequent `static_destruct()`, skip calling `freep()` on this argument if it was already freed.                                                                         
                                - We implement this by adding a simple already_freed flag into the perargument state (for example, a `bool arg_freed` alongside `char *arg_root`), and modify                 
                             the staticdestructor registration to consult that flag before invoking `freep()`.                                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Implementation Steps                                                                                                                                                             
                                - In the source file that declares the global `char *arg_root` (and/or other `*arg_*` used by `systemctl_parse_argv`), introduce a corresponding `static bool                    
                             arg_root_freed = false;`.                                                                                                                                                           
                                - When the harness (or normal code) registers the destructor for `&arg_root`, also register code that checks:                                                                    
                                     if (!arg_root_freed)                                                                                                                                                        
                                           freep(&arg_root);                                                                                                                                                     
                                - In `parse_path_argument()`:                                                                                                                                                    
                                   Immediately after `*arg = mfree(*arg)` (emptypath branch) or after `free_and_replace(*arg, p)`, set `arg_root_freed = true;`                                                
                                     This ensures that if we freed `arg_root` already while parsing, the static destructor will see `arg_root_freed == true` and skip the second free.                          
                                - At the very end of `systemctl_parse_argv()` (i.e. after all calls to `parse_path_argument()` have completed successfully or errored):                                          
                                   Reset `arg_root_freed = false;` so that in the _next_ invocation of the harness (next fuzz iteration) the destructor will run as normal.                                     
                                - This approach confines all ownershiptracking to the existing source, and leaves the staticdestruct harness intact.                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Why This Works & Mitigates Side Effects                                                                                                                                          
                                - We preserve existing freeandreplace semantics: every time `parse_path_argument()` frees or replaces the old buffer, normal inprocess logic sees the buffer                  
                             disappear and we account for it.                                                                                                                                                    
                                - The static destructor remains responsible for cleaning up any buffer that survives parsing (i.e. the pointer left in `arg_root`), but will *not* free pointers                 
                             that were already freed earlier in the same run.                                                                                                                                    
                                - Because we reset the freed flag at the end of each harness iteration, we do not disturb subsequent runs or system shutdown cleanup.                                          
                                - There is minimal risk of memory leakage because every code path either sets the freed flag or leaves the final pointer available for `static_destruct` to free                 
                             on exit.                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. Alternative Considerations                                                                                                                                                       
                                - One might try to deregister the destructor entry at parsetime, but that would require intimate changes to the `__start_SYSTEMD_STATIC_DESTRUCT` list or                       
                             reliance on nonpublic APIs.                                                                                                                                                        
                                - We avoid any changes to the harness, any broad exceptioncatching, or removal of the bufferfreeing logic.                                                                     
                                - We do not introduce new memory leaks since every pointer either gets freed by the parser or by static teardown (but never twice).                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             7. Testing & Validation                                                                                                                                                             
                                - Add new libFuzzer corpus entry for empty and nonempty paths to ensure no doublefree.                                                                                         
                                - Rerun AddressSanitizer under `fuzz-systemctl-parse-argv` for 1000+ iterations to confirm the doublefree no longer appears.                                                   
                                - Validate a normal systemd shutdown path still frees `arg_root` exactly once.                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             8. Next Steps                                                                                                                                                                       
                                - Implement the above flags in `src/systemctl/systemctl.c` (where `arg_root` is declared).                                                                                       
                                - Patch `static-destruct.h` registration code so that we can pass the arg_root_freed flag into the destructor.                                                                 
                                - Run the full systemd test suite to ensure no regressions.                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             By tracking on a perargument basis whether the buffer has already been freed during parsing, and gating the static destructor accordingly, we eliminate the                        
                             doublefree without altering the harness or broad systemd teardown logic. This targeted change is minimal, localized, and preserves all existing functionality.                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===

                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             The initial issue is an AddressSanitizer double-free detected when fuzzing `systemctl_parse_argv`, specifically in `parse_path_argument`                                            
                             (src/shared/parse-argument.c:68). The fuzzer run shows that the same heap allocation is freed twiceonce in `parse_path_argument` and again in the fuzz harnesss                   
                             `static_destruct` call in `run_once`.                                                                                                                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             An attempted patch replaced explicit `mfree` calls with the `free_and_replace` helper macro to centralize the free-and-nullify logic:                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ```diff                                                                                                                                                                             
                             -       if (isempty(path)) {                                                                                                                                                        
                             -               *arg = mfree(*arg);                                                                                                                                                 
                             -               return 0;                                                                                                                                                           
                             -       }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             +       if (isempty(path))                                                                                                                                                          
                             +               return free_and_replace(*arg, NULL);                                                                                                                                
                             ...                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             -       if (suppress_root && empty_or_root(p))                                                                                                                                      
                             -               p = mfree(p);                                                                                                                                                       
                             +       if (suppress_root && empty_or_root(p))                                                                                                                                      
                             +               return free_and_replace(*arg, NULL);                                                                                                                                
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             After applying the patch, the build fails with errors indicating that `free_and_replace(*arg, NULL)` cannot be used because the macro tries to take the address of                  
                             its second argument (an rvalue `NULL`), e.g.:                                                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             error: cannot take the address of an rvalue of type 'void *'                                                                                                                        
                                return free_and_replace(*arg, NULL);                                                                                                                                             
                                       ^                      ~~~~                                                                                                                                               
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. **Initial Issue**                                                                                                                                                                
                                - Fuzzer invocation: `fuzz-systemctl-parse-argv` exercised `systemctl_parse_argv`, which calls `parse_path_argument`.                                                            
                                - AddressSanitizer report:                                                                                                                                                       
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                  ERROR: AddressSanitizer: attempting double-free on 0x502000007310                                                                                                              
                                    #1 parse_path_argument  parse-argument.c:68:24                                                                                                                              
                                    #2 systemctl_parse_argv  systemctl.c:732:29                                                                                                                                 
                                    #3 run_once  fuzz-systemctl-parse-argv.c:58:13                                                                                                                              
                                    #1 static_destruct  static-destruct.h:95:25    second free                                                                                                                 
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - The report clearly shows the first free in `parse_path_argument` and a second free of the same pointer in `static_destruct` at the end of each fuzz iteration.                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. **Important Observations**                                                                                                                                                       
                                - The pointer freed in `parse_path_argument` is stored in `*arg`, which the harness later frees unconditionally via `static_destruct`.                                           
                                - The memory allocation originates in `path_make_absolute_cwd`/`path_extend_internal`, so ownership must be carefully managed.                                                   
                                - The harnesss clean-up logic assumes `*arg` may still hold a heap pointer, leading to the second free.                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. **Patch Attempt**                                                                                                                                                                
                                - Goal: unify free-and-nullify behaviour via `free_and_replace(a, b)` instead of manual `mfree`.                                                                                 
                                - Changes applied at two early-exit points in `parse_path_argument`:                                                                                                             
                                  ```diff                                                                                                                                                                        
                                  if (isempty(path))                                                                                                                                                             
                             -       *arg = mfree(*arg);                                                                                                                                                         
                             -       return 0;                                                                                                                                                                   
                             +       return free_and_replace(*arg, NULL);                                                                                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                  ...                                                                                                                                                                            
                                  if (suppress_root && empty_or_root(p))                                                                                                                                         
                             -       p = mfree(p);                                                                                                                                                               
                             +       return free_and_replace(*arg, NULL);                                                                                                                                        
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - The patch removes the manual `mfree` and uses the macro to free and set `*arg` to `NULL` in one step.                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. **Post-Patch Build Errors**                                                                                                                                                      
                                - Compiler errors in `alloc-util.h`:                                                                                                                                             
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                  error: cannot take the address of an rvalue of type 'void *'                                                                                                                   
                                     return free_and_replace(*arg, NULL);                                                                                                                                        
                                            ^                      ~~~~                                                                                                                                          
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - The `free_and_replace_full` macro expands to code that does:                                                                                                                   
                                  ```c                                                                                                                                                                           
                                  typeof(b)* _b = &(b);                                                                                                                                                          
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                  but `b` is `NULL` (an rvalue), so `&(NULL)` is invalid C.                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. **Areas for Further Investigation**                                                                                                                                              
                                - **parse_path_argument (src/shared/parse-argument.c)**                                                                                                                          
                                   Verify all exit paths consistently free or transfer ownership of memory.                                                                                                     
                                   Clarify the intended ownership model for `*arg` when return value is zero vs non-zero.                                                                                       
                                - **free_and_replace Macro (src/basic/alloc-util.h)**                                                                                                                            
                                   Understand constraints on its argumentsespecially that the second argument must be an lvalue.                                                                               
                                   Check other call sites for correct usage patterns.                                                                                                                           
                                - **Fuzz Harness Clean-up (src/shared/static-destruct.h & fuzz-systemctl-parse-argv.c)**                                                                                         
                                   Review how `static_destruct` frees residual pointers in `run_once`.                                                                                                          
                                   Ensure no double-free occurs when caller has already freed or nullified `*arg`.                                                                                              
                                - **path_make_absolute_cwd and path_extend_internal (src/basic/path-util.c)**                                                                                                    
                                   Examine how reallocation is used and returned, and how error or empty cases are handled.                                                                                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             A holistic review of memory ownership in argument parsing and in the fuzz harnesss teardown routine is recommended to fully understand and resolve the double-free                 
                             and to correct the patch so it compiles and preserves correct behavior.

                             100:         * unset a pointer from a _cleanup_ function. */

                             107:}                                                                                                                                                                               
                             108:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             109:#define _cleanup_free_ _cleanup_(freep)                                                                                                                                         
                             110:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             111:static inline bool size_multiply_overflow(size_t size, size_t need) {                                                                                                           
                             112:        return _unlikely_(need != 0 && size > (SIZE_MAX / need));                                                                                                               
                             113:}                                                                                                                                                                               
                             114:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             115:_malloc_ _alloc_(1, 2) static inline void *malloc_multiply(size_t need, size_t size) {                                                                                          
                             116:        if (size_multiply_overflow(size, need))                                                                                                                                 
                             117:                return NULL;                                                                                                                                                    
                             118:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             119:        return malloc(size * need ?: 1);                                                                                                                                        
                             120:}

                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             src/shared/parse-argument.c:55-81                                                                                                                                                   
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             55:int parse_path_argument(const char *path, bool suppress_root, char **arg) {                                                                                                      
                             56:        char *p;                                                                                                                                                                 
                             57:        int r;                                                                                                                                                                   
                             58:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             59:        /*                                                                                                                                                                       
                             60:         * This function is intended to be used in command line parsers, to handle paths that are passed                                                                         
                             61:         * in. It makes the path absolute, and reduces it to NULL if omitted or root (the latter optionally).

                             550:         * end/begin already with one so that it is unnecessary. Note that slashes which are already                                                                            
                             551:         * duplicate won't be removed. The string returned is hence always equal to or longer than the sum of                                                                   
                             552:         * the lengths of the individual strings.                                                                                                                               
                             553:         *                                                                                                                                                                      
                             554:         * The first argument may be an already allocated string that is extended via realloc() if                                                                              
                             555:         * non-NULL. path_extend() and path_join() are macro wrappers around this function, making use of the                                                                   
                             556:         * first parameter to distinguish the two operations.                                                                                                                   
                             557:         *                                                                                                                                                                      
                             558:         * Note: any listed empty string is simply skipped. This can be useful for concatenating strings of                                                                     
                             559:         * which some are optional.                                                                                                                                             
                             560:         *                                                                                                                                                                      
                             561:         * Examples:                                                                                                                                                            
                             562:         *                                                                                                                                                                      
                             563:         * path_join("foo", "bar")  "foo/bar"                                                                                                                                  
                             564:         * path_join("foo/", "bar")  "foo/bar"                                                                                                                                 
                             565:         * path_join("", "foo", "", "bar", "")  "foo/bar" */                                                                                                                   
                             566:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             567:        sz = old_sz = x ? strlen_ptr(*x) : 0;                                                                                                                                   
                             568:        va_start(ap, x);                                                                                                                                                        
                             569:        while ((p = va_arg(ap, char*)) != POINTER_MAX) {                                                                                                                        
                             570:                size_t add;                                                                                                                                                     
                             571:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             572:                if (isempty(p))                                                                                                                                                 
                             573:                        continue;                                                                                                                                               
                             574:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             575:                add = 1 + strlen(p);                                                                                                                                            
                             576:                if (sz > SIZE_MAX - add) { /* overflow check */                                                                                                                 
                             577:                        va_end(ap);                                                                                                                                             
                             578:                        return NULL;                                                                                                                                            
                             579:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             580:

                             582:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             583:        va_end(ap);                                                                                                                                                             
                             584:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             585:        nx = realloc(x ? *x : NULL, GREEDY_ALLOC_ROUND_UP(sz+1));                                                                                                               
                             586:        if (!nx)                                                                                                                                                                
                             587:                return NULL;                                                                                                                                                    
                             588:        if (x)                                                                                                                                                                  
                             589:                *x = nx;

                             591:        if (old_sz > 0)                                                                                                                                                         
                             592:                slash = nx[old_sz-1] == '/';                                                                                                                                    
                             593:        else {                                                                                                                                                                  
                             594:                nx[old_sz] = 0;                                                                                                                                                 
                             595:                slash = true; /* no need to generate a slash anymore */                                                                                                         
                             596:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             597:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             598:        q = nx + old_sz;                                                                                                                                                        
                             599:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             600:        va_start(ap, x);                                                                                                                                                        
                             601:        while ((p = va_arg(ap, char*)) != POINTER_MAX) {                                                                                                                        
                             602:                if (isempty(p))                                                                                                                                                 
                             603:                        continue;                                                                                                                                               
                             604:

                             606:                        *(q++) = '/';                                                                                                                                           
                             607:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             608:                q = stpcpy(q, p);                                                                                                                                               
                             609:                slash = endswith(p, "/");                                                                                                                                       
                             610:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             611:        va_end(ap);                                                                                                                                                             
                             612:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             613:        return nx;
