                             /tasks/4d0b56e5-fc68-40e3-9f6e-e14e62699c8b/fuzz-tooling/build/out/systemd:/out -v /tmp/tmpdgh60sav:/testcase -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.3.0 reproduce                  
                             fuzz-systemctl-parse-argv -runs=100.                                                                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             A double-free is detected when fuzzing the `systemctl_parse_argv` path-parsing logic. AddressSanitizer reports that a buffer is freed twice inside                                  
                             `parse_path_argument()`, under certain input conditions. A patch attempt was made in `src/shared/parse-argument.c` to replace one free with `mfree()` and to null                   
                             out `*arg`, and to add a similar cleanup in the suppress_root branch. Despite these changes, the double-free still occurs at the same site in                                     
                             `parse_path_argument()`, indicating the patch did not cover all free paths.                                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Initial issue                                                                                                                                                                       
                             - Running the libFuzzer harness for `fuzz-systemctl-parse-argv` triggers an AddressSanitizer error:                                                                                 
                               attempting double-free on 0x502000007310 in thread T0.                                                                                                                          
                             - Stack trace shows the first free in `parse_path_argument()` at line 68, and a second free of the same pointer in `static_destruct()` called from the fuzzing                      
                             harnesss `run_once()` routine.                                                                                                                                                     
                             - The allocated region was originally created via `realloc()` in `path_extend_internal()  path_make_absolute_cwd()  parse_path_argument()`.                                       
                             - The double-free is reproducible in the fuzz run, aborting the harness.                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Important observations                                                                                                                                                              
                             1. The double-free always points to `parse_path_argument()` line 68.                                                                                                                
                             2. A second free comes from the fuzz harnesss cleanup code (`static_destruct()`), indicating ownership of `*arg` is ambiguous.                                                     
                             3. Both the isempty(path) branch and the suppress_root && empty_or_root(p) branch in `parse_path_argument()` may prematurely free `*arg` without preventing the                 
                             harness from freeing it again.                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Patch attempt                                                                                                                                                                       
                             - In `src/shared/parse-argument.c`, the patch modifies `parse_path_argument()` as follows:                                                                                          
                               * In the `if (isempty(path))` block (originally `*arg = mfree(*arg)`), split into `mfree(*arg); *arg = NULL; return 0;`.                                                          
                               * In the `if (suppress_root && empty_or_root(p))` block, add:                                                                                                                     
                                 ```                                                                                                                                                                             
                                 mfree(p);                                                                                                                                                                       
                                 mfree(*arg);                                                                                                                                                                    
                                 *arg = NULL;                                                                                                                                                                    
                                 return 0;                                                                                                                                                                       
                                 ```                                                                                                                                                                             
                             - Aim: ensure `*arg` is set to NULL after free, and avoid the harness freeing it a second time.                                                                                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Log after patch                                                                                                                                                                     
                             - The fuzz run still fails with an AddressSanitizer double-free at the same location:                                                                                               
                               ```                                                                                                                                                                               
                               AddressSanitizer: attempting double-free in parse_path_argument (/src/.../parse-argument.c:68:17)                                                                                 
                               freed by thread T0 here:                                                                                                                                                          
                                   #1 static_destruct ... run_once                                                                                                                                               
                               previously allocated by thread T0 here:                                                                                                                                           
                                   #1 path_extend_internal  path_make_absolute_cwd  parse_path_argument                                                                                                        
                               ```                                                                                                                                                                               
                             - This confirms the patch did not prevent the second free of the same memory region.                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Areas for further investigation                                                                                                                                                     
                             - The memory ownership semantics of `*arg`: which code paths free it, and which expect to free it later?                                                                            
                             - The `free_and_replace()` helper that returns `free(old), new`does it overlap with other frees?                                                                                   
                             - The harness cleanup in `static_destruct()` and how it interacts with `parse_path_argument()` on each test iteration.                                                              
                             - The logic in `path-util.c`, especially `path_extend_internal()` and `path_make_absolute_cwd()`, to confirm when and where reallocd buffers are transferred or                    
                             freed.                                                                                                                                                                              
                             - Any other callers of `parse_path_argument()` or patterns where `*arg` may be freed more than once.                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log

                             15:#include "systemctl-util.h"                                                                                                                                                      
                             16:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             17:static int run_once(const uint8_t *data, size_t size) {                                                                                                                          
                             18:        _cleanup_strv_free_ char **argv = NULL;                                                                                                                                  
                             19:        _cleanup_close_ int orig_stdout_fd = -EBADF;                                                                                                                             
                             20:        int r;                                                                                                                                                                   
                             21:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             22:        if (size > 16*1024)                                                                                                                                                      
                             23:                return 0; /* See the comment below about the limit for strv_length(). */                                                                                         
                             24:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             25:        fuzz_setup_logging();                                                                                                                                                    
                             26:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             27:        arg_pager_flags = PAGER_DISABLE; /* We shouldn't execute the pager */                                                                                                    
                             28:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             29:        argv = strv_parse_nulstr((const char *)data, size);                                                                                                                      
                             30:        if (!argv)                                                                                                                                                               
                             31:                return log_oom();                                                                                                                                                
                             32:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             33:        if (!argv[0])                                                                                                                                                            
                             34:                return 0; /* argv[0] should always be present, but may be zero-length. */                                                                                        
                             35:        if (strv_length(argv) > 1024)                                                                                                                                            
                             36:                return 0; /* oss-fuzz reports timeouts which are caused by appending to a very long strv.                                                                        
                             37:                           * The code is indeed not very efficient, but it's designed for normal command-line                                                                    
                             38:                           * use, where we don't expect more than a dozen of entries. The fact that it is                                                                        
                             39:                           * slow with ~100k entries is not particularly interesting. Let's just refuse such                                                                     
                             40:                           * long command lines. */                                                                                                                              
                             41:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             42:        if (getenv_bool("SYSTEMD_FUZZ_OUTPUT") <= 0) {                                                                                                                           
                             43:                orig_stdout_fd = fcntl(fileno(stdout), F_DUPFD_CLOEXEC, 3);                                                                                                      
                             44:                if (orig_stdout_fd < 0)                                                                                                                                          
                             45:                        log_warning_errno(orig_stdout_fd, "Failed to duplicate fd 1: %m");                                                                                       
                             46:                else                                                                                                                                                             
                             47:                        assert_se(freopen("/dev/null", "w", stdout));                                                                                                            
                             48:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             49:                opterr = 0; /* do not print errors */                                                                                                                            
                             50:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             51:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             52:        /* We need to reset some global state manually here since libfuzzer feeds a single process with                                                                          
                             53:         * multiple inputs, so we might carry over state from previous invocations that can trigger                                                                              
                             54:         * certain asserts. */                                                                                                                                                   
                             55:        optind = 0; /* this tells the getopt machinery to reinitialize */                                                                                                        
                             56:        arg_transport = BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL;                                                                                                                                     
                             57:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             58:        r = systemctl_dispatch_parse_argv(strv_length(argv), argv);                                                                                                              
                             59:        if (r < 0)                                                                                                                                                               
                             60:                log_error_errno(r, "Failed to parse args: %m");                                                                                                                  
                             61:        else                                                                                                                                                                     
                             62:                log_info(r == 0 ? "Done!" : "Action!");                                                                                                                          
                             63:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             64:        if (orig_stdout_fd >= 0)                                                                                                                                                 
                             65:                assert_se(freopen(FORMAT_PROC_FD_PATH(orig_stdout_fd), "w", stdout));                                                                                            
                             66:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             67:        release_busses(); /* We open the bus for communication with logind.                                                                                                      
                             68:                           * It needs to be closed to avoid apparent leaks. */                                                                                                   
                             69:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             70:        mac_selinux_finish();                                                                                                                                                    
                             71:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             72:        /* Call static destructors to do global state cleanup. We do it here, and not in fuzz-main.c so that                                                                     
                             73:         * any global state is destroyed between fuzzer runs. */                                                                                                                 
                             74:        static_destruct();                                                                                                                                                       
                             75:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             76:        return 0;                                                                                                                                                                
                             77:}                                                                                                                                                                                
                             78:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             79:int LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput(const uint8_t *data, size_t size) {                                                                                                                   
                             80:        if (size == 0) return 0;                                                                                                                                                 
                             81:        uint8_t num_iter = data[0];                                                                                                                                              
                             82:        data++;                                                                                                                                                                  
                             83:        size -= 1;                                                                                                                                                               
                             84:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             85:        for (int i = 0; i < num_iter; i++) {                                                                                                                                     
                             86:                run_once(data, size);                                                                                                                                            
                             87:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             88:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             89:        return 0;                                                                                                                                                                
                             90:}                                                                                                                                                                                
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             src/systemctl/systemctl.c:729-740

                             729:                        break;                                                                                                                                                  
                             730:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             731:                case ARG_ROOT:                                                                                                                                                  
                             732:                        r = parse_path_argument(optarg, false, &arg_root);                                                                                                      
                             733:                        if (r < 0)                                                                                                                                              
                             734:                                return r;                                                                                                                                       
                             735:                        break;                                                                                                                                                  
                             736:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             737:                case ARG_IMAGE:                                                                                                                                                 
                             738:                        r = parse_path_argument(optarg, false, &arg_image);                                                                                                     
                             739:                        if (r < 0)                                                                                                                                              
                             740:                                return r;                                                                                                                                       
                             ```

                             145:static int systemctl_help(void) {

                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             src/basic/alloc-util.h:98-110                                                                                                                                                       
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             98:static inline void unsetp(void *p) {                                                                                                                                             
                             99:        /* A trivial "destructor" that can be used in cases where we want to                                                                                                     
                             100:         * unset a pointer from a _cleanup_ function. */                                                                                                                        
                             101:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             102:        *(void**)p = NULL;                                                                                                                                                      
                             103:}                                                                                                                                                                               
                             104:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             105:static inline void freep(void *p) {                                                                                                                                             
                             106:        free(*(void**) p);                                                                                                                                                      
                             107:}                                                                                                                                                                               
                             108:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             109:#define _cleanup_free_ _cleanup_(freep)                                                                                                                                         
                             110:
